    <!--                  SECTION TWO: GEOMETRIC CONSTRUCTIONS           -->
    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->

    <string name="SectionTwoTheoryDef_9">• Geometric construction uses only a ruler and compass.
\n • The ruler draws lines, the compass marks circles and segments.
\n • Problems are solved through precise constructions.</string>

    <string name="SectionTwoTheoryDefQuestion_9">How many tools are used in classical geometric construction?</string>
    <string name="SectionTwoTheoryDefAnswerOne_9">1</string>
    <string name="SectionTwoTheoryDefAnswerTwo_9">2</string>
    <string name="SectionTwoTheoryDefAnswerThree_9">3</string>
    <string name="SectionTwoTheoryDefCorrectAnswer_9">2</string>

    <string name="SectionTwoTheoryProperties_9">• The ruler draws lines but doesn\'t measure lengths.
\n • The compass transfers distances between points.
\n • Both tools define classic constructions.</string>

    <string name="SectionTwoTheoryPropsQuestion_9">Does the ruler measure lengths in classical geometric construction?</string>
    <string name="SectionTwoTheoryPropsAnswerOne_9">True</string>
    <string name="SectionTwoTheoryPropsAnswerTwo_9">False</string>
    <string name="SectionTwoTheoryPropsAnswerThree_9"></string>
    <string name="SectionTwoTheoryPropsCorrectAnswer_9">False</string>

    <string name="SectionTwoTheoryWorkedExamples_9">• To construct a triangle with sides a, b, c: draw segment AB = a, then draw a circle of radius b centred at A and a circle of radius c centred at B. Their intersection gives point C, completing the triangle.
\n • To bisect angle BAC: place the compass at A and mark equal arcs on AB and AC, getting points D and E. Then draw arcs of equal radius from D and E; their intersection F gives the bisecting ray AF.
\n • The bisecting ray AF divides angle BAC into two equal angles, confirmed by the congruence of triangles ADF and AEF.</string>

    <string name="SectionTwoTheoryWorkedExQuestion_9">How many equal-radius arcs from the vertex are drawn to begin bisecting an angle?</string>
    <string name="SectionTwoTheoryWorkedExAnswerOne_9">1</string>
    <string name="SectionTwoTheoryWorkedExAnswerTwo_9">2</string>
    <string name="SectionTwoTheoryWorkedExAnswerThree_9">3</string>
    <string name="SectionTwoTheoryWorkedExCorrectAnswer_9">2</string>

